{[%evp 0,97,19,31,14,30,28,18,18,12,58,50,26,13,15,14,17,10,40,24,66,14,27,26,
26,7,13,-20,0,43,73,73,84,-10,76,76,50,-71,0,-32,29,29,168,110,81,81,81,57,126,
52,189,104,186,88,122,97,63,67,178,178,193,152,134,88,201,186,208,448,653,210,
735,128,122,112,115,112,83,71,89,90,204,35,38,34,59,99,93,93,106,106,212,200,
317,362,331,332,483,331,332,200] It's very important to know that if Black
plays ...b7-b6 too early, White can always consider the option of Bb5+. This
annoying move manages to considerably spoil Black's coordination. Let's take a
look at an example. Bb5 check ...and typical ideas once again} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3
e6 3. Bg5 d5 4. e3 b6 $6 {Played to early, this move is a concession.} ({
The same innacuracy can be exectued under a different move order -} 4... Be7 5.
Nbd2 c5 6. c3 b6 7. Bb5+ $1 {Since Black hasn't castled yet, this move is very
annoying for Black. It turns out that Black cannot neutralize this check
without committing concessions.} Bd7 {The d7-square is not a good spot for the
bishop. In this structure, Black would rather prefer to put it on b7.} ({
The attempt to exchange the light-squared bishops by means of} 7... Nfd7 8. Bf4
Ba6 {is well met by} 9. a4 {when Black has problems to untangle.}) ({It goes
without saying that} 7... Nbd7 $4 {is losing on the spot after} 8. Bc6 Rb8 9.
Bf4 $18) 8. Bd3 O-O 9. Ne5 Nc6 {At this point, White has a pleasant choice.}
10. f4 {This natural move always works when Black cannot make use of the
e4-square.} ({Another possibility is} 10. Nxc6 Bxc6 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. f4 {
As we already know, without knights, Black does not have enough counterplay.})
({Of course,} 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. f4 {is also a decent option.})) 5. Nbd2 Bb7 6.
Bb5+ $1 {Once again, this is the right decision. White immediately grabs his
chance.} c6 {Black has nothing better.} ({After} 6... Nbd7 $4 7. Ne5 Bc8 8. Nc6
$18 {Black is losing the queen.}) ({Obviously, after} 6... Bc6 7. Bd3 {Black
will spend a tempo on ...Bb7 since the bishop is misplaced on c6.}) 7. Bd3 Nbd7
8. Ne5 Qc8 9. f4 {Now, we can clearly see the point behind Bb5+. Having
provoked ...c7-c6, White does not need to reckon with the thematic ...Ne4
resource.} g6 10. Qf3 $1 Bg7 11. O-O O-O 12. Qh3 $6 {This move is already an
inaccuracy. White weakens his control of the e4-square.} (12. c3 $3 {This is
the right move! Do not lose sight of the e4-square...unless you are very sure
what you are doing!!!} c5 13. g4 $1 {Since the centre is stable, White can
start his kingside pawn expansion.} ({Another idea is to start with} 13. Rf2 $3
{in order to avoid the possible exchange of the light-squared bishops. A
possible continuation would be} Ba6 14. Bc2 Qc7 15. Re1 Rac8 16. g4 $18 {
White has an overwhelming attack.}) 13... Qc7 14. Bxf6 $1 {This exchange comes
just in time since the bishop is on the way of the kingside pawns.} Nxf6 15. g5
Nd7 16. h4 {It turns out that Black has no way of neutralizing White's attack.}
Nxe5 ({Another possibility is} 16... f6 {This move, however, weakens the
kingside -} 17. gxf6 Bxf6 18. Qg4 Rae8 19. h5 {White's attack is very strong.})
17. fxe5 Rac8 18. Qg2 a6 19. Nf3 $1 {[%cal Gf3h2,Gh2g4,Gg4f6] White is
planning to bring the knight all the way to f6 via the g4-square.} ({The
positional exchange sacrifice} 19. Rf6 {would be another decent possibility.})
19... b5 {Black's queenside counterplay turns out to be largely insufficient.}
20. Nh2 $1 b4 21. Ng4 bxc3 22. bxc3 cxd4 23. cxd4 Qc3 24. Rad1 Rc7 25. Nf6+
Bxf6 (25... Kh8 26. h5) 26. gxf6 {White is already winning since the black
king is in a mating net.}) 12... c5 13. Ndf3 $6 {No, not like that! Although,
White is still a bit better!} Ne4 14. Bh6 Ndf6 15. Ng5 Nd6 16. Ng4 Nh5 17. Bxg7
Kxg7 18. Nxh7 Rh8 19. Ng5 f5 20. Ne5 Nxf4 21. Qg3 Nh5 22. Qe1 Nf6 23. dxc5 bxc5
24. c4 Re8 25. Rc1 Qd8 26. Qg3 Nh5 27. Qh4 Qf6 28. Nd7 Qe7 29. Nxc5 Bc8 30.
cxd5 exd5 31. Qd4+ Nf6 32. Rf3 Nde4 33. Bxe4 fxe4 34. Rf4 Qe5 35. Qxe5 Rxe5 36.
h4 Bf5 37. Nb3 Rc8 38. Rff1 Ng4 39. Rxc8 Bxc8 40. Rc1 Re8 41. Rc7+ Kg8 42. Nd4
Nxe3 43. Nc6 Nf5 44. g4 Nd6 45. Ne7+ Kh8 46. Nxg6+ Kg8 47. Ne7+ Kh8 48. Ng6+
Kg8 49. h5 1-0

