young greek player. After Black's common mistake of cxd4? in connecton with d5
....(If black's pawn was still on d6 or d7, then cd4 is ok)} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3
e6 3. Bg5 h6 4. Bh4 c5 5. e3 Nc6 6. Nbd2 a6 $2 {Dont do that in the Torre!
