{[%evp 0,45,23,20,27,17,17,7,17,-5,13,13,35,25,48,5,45,24,21,20,20,11,32,30,38,
39,32,36,41,-23,-11,-20,-31,-49,-30,-22,-18,-18,-17,-21,-21,-5,-27,-27,0,41,
297,310] The Ba6 lines ....They are not a problem at all for us! ..he only
problem is that...we do not play for checkmate without our Bd3...however white
is still doing great......dont forget to open op the center and the queenside
with c4...but DO NOT CREATE AN ISOLATED PAWN! ...TAKE BACK ON c4 AND d4 ALWAYS
WITH THE KNIGHTS !!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 h6 (3... c5 4. e3 b6 $2 5. d5
$1) 4. Bh4 b6 5. Nbd2 (5. e3) 5... c5 (5... Ba6 6. e4 (6. Bxf6 Qxf6 7. e4 Bxf1
8. Kxf1 g6 9. c3 Bg7 10. g3 O-O 11. Kg2) (6. e3 Bxf1 7. Nxf1) 6... Bxf1 7. Kxf1
Be7 8. Bxf6 Bxf6 9. c3 O-O 10. g3) 6. e3 Be7 7. Bd3 Ba6 8. Bxa6 Nxa6 9. O-O O-O
10. c3 (10. Qe2 Nc7 11. Rfd1 (11. Rad1) (11. c4 $1 cxd4 (11... d5 12. Rfd1 $16
Rc8 (12... dxc4 13. Nxc4 cxd4 14. Nxd4 {ALWAYS WITH THE KNIGHTS !!}) 13. dxc5 (
13. h3) (13. Rac1) 13... bxc5 14. Rac1 Nh5 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Ne5 Nf6 17. Ndf3
$14 (17. e4 d4 18. f4 Nd7 19. Nxd7 Qxd7 20. e5 $14)) 12. Nxd4 $1 d5 (12... Nfe8
13. Bg3) 13. Nc6 Qd7 14. Nxe7+ Qxe7 15. Rac1) 11... cxd4 12. exd4 (12. Nxd4
Nfe8 (12... Qc8 13. c4 (13. Qf3 Re8 14. c4 Rb8 15. Rac1 a6 16. Nb1) 13... Qb7
14. Qf3) 13. Bg3 Bf6 14. N2f3 (14. Ne4) 14... Qe7 15. c4)) 10... Qc7 11. Rc1 $5
(11. Qe2 Qb7 12. a4 (12. e4 $1 Rfe8 13. a3 (13. e5 Nd5 14. Bxe7 Rxe7 15. Nc4
$16)) 12... cxd4 13. exd4 Nc7 14. Ne5) 11... Qb7 12. Qe2 d5 {i dont really
like that...because we cannot play c4 after this move!} 13. Ne5 (13. c4 $1 dxc4
14. Nxc4 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Nc5 16. b4 $3 Nce4 (16... Ncd7 17. b5 $3 a6 (17... Bc5
18. Nc6 a6 19. a4 axb5 20. axb5 Ra4 21. Rfd1 (21. Bxf6 $5) 21... Rfa8 22. Qf3
$18) 18. Nc6 Rfe8 19. Bxf6 (19. Nxe7+ Rxe7 20. Nd6 Qb8 21. Rc8+) (19. a4 axb5
20. axb5 $16) 19... Nxf6 20. a4 axb5 21. axb5) 17. b5 Rac8 (17... a6 18. a4
axb5 19. axb5 Ra4 20. Nc6 $16) 18. Nc6 Rfe8 19. Bxf6 Nxf6 20. Rfd1 Nd7 21. a4
Ne5 22. g3 Nxc4 23. Qxc4 Bc5 24. a5 (24. Rd2) 24... a6 (24... Rc7 25. a6))
13... Rac8 14. c4 $6 {no need to create an isolated pawn!} (14. c4) (14. a4) (
14. f4 $5) 14... cxd4 15. exd4 dxc4 16. Ndxc4 Rfd8 (16... Nc7 17. Bxf6) 17.
Rfd1 Nb4 18. a3 Nbd5 $15 19. Qf3 Rc7 (19... Qb8 20. b4 Rc7 (20... b5 21. Na5) (
