for Black)} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. d4 e6 3. Bg5 Be7 4. Nbd2 d5 5. e3 O-O 6. Bd3 Nbd7 7.
c3 $1 (7. Ne5 $6 Nxe5 8. dxe5 Nd7 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. f4 Nc5 $1 $132) 7... c5 8.
Ne5 $1 h6 9. Bf4 $3 $16 (9. h4 $3 $16) 9... Qb6 10. Rb1 $1 $16 {as always 1...
Qb6 2.Rb1!} Bd6 11. Bg3 $5 (11. Nec4 $1 dxc4 12. Nxc4 Qc6 13. Nxd6 cxd4 14.
exd4 Qxg2 15. Rf1 Rd8 16. Qe2 $16) 11... cxd4 $2 (11... Qc7 12. f4 b6 13. O-O
Bb7 14. Qf3 Rac8 15. Bh4 $16 a6 16. g4) 12. exd4 Bxe5 13. Bxe5 $5 $16 (13. dxe5
Nc5 14. Bc2 Nfe4 15. O-O Nxg3 16. hxg3 $16) 13... Nxe5 14. dxe5 Nd7 15. Nf3 Nc5
16. O-O $1 $16 Bd7 (16... Nxd3 17. Qxd3 Bd7 18. Nd4 Rac8 (18... a6 19. Rfe1 $3
{Be aware of this trick...We should avoid trading the powerful knight with his
bad bishop !!} (19. Qe2 $4 Bb5 $3 $15 20. Nxb5 Qxb5 21. Qxb5 axb5 22. a3 Ra4 $3
) 19... Bb5 20. Qd2 $18 (20. Qg3 $16) 20... Rac8 21. Re3 Rfe8 22. Rbe1) 19.
Rfe1 $16) 17. Nd4 Rac8 18. Re1 a5 19. Bc2 a4 20. a3 $3 {We do not allow
counterplay whenever this is possible!!} Bb5 21. Re3 $1 {black is lost....f5
or not f5} f5 (21... Rc7 22. Qd2 Kh8 23. Rbe1 Be8 24. Bb1) 22. exf6 Rxf6 23.
Qg4 (23. b3 $3 axb3 24. Bxb3 $18) 23... Bc4 24. Rbe1 Rcf8 25. Rg3 Qc7 26. Rf3
e5 27. Rxf6 Rxf6 28. Qg3 Rf4 29. Nf5 Kf7 30. Qxg7+ 1-0

