10,109,111,100,104,71,65,65,64,64,62,79,36,64,60,51,61,65,52,113,118,141,155,
218,245,253,250,267,286,376,376,390,384,651,673,673,709,709,793,811,831,839,
843,843,865,1051,1082,1118,779,963,642] Let's now take a brief look at a
thematic game featuring the setup with ...Qb6.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 c5
4. e3 Qb6 5. Qc1 {As we already know, this move is completely playable but
White needs to know some concrete lines in order to neutralize Black's
immediate counterplay.} ({Of course, I still prefer} 5. Nbd2) 5... Nc6 6. c3
cxd4 {In my opinion, this move is premature since after} 7. exd4 {the
