that the structure arising after} 7... Be7 8. Nbd2 O-O 9. Bd3 Qc7 10. O-O d5
11. Qd1 {[%cal Gd1e2,Gf3e5] is clearly in White's favour.}) 8. Bd3 $1 {If you
play the line with 5.Qc1, never forget to first develop the kingside.} ({
I repeat that} 8. Nbd2 $2 {is well met by} e5 $3 9. dxe5 Ng4) 8... Ne4 9. O-O {
White just proceed with the development. Nevertheless, there are many good
alternatives in this position.} ({A very natural move would be} 9. Bf4 {
when it turns out that Black's activity is only temporary.}) ({Since Black
played ...cxd4 too early, another good option is} 9. Be3 {The opposition along
the diagonal g1-a7 can be annoying for Black. For example, White can often use
the idea Bxe4 followed by d4-d5. The attempt to build a Stonewall structure
with} Bd6 10. O-O O-O 11. Nbd2 f5 {does not work quite well} ({After} 11...
Nxd2 12. Qxd2 f6 {White should play} 13. c4 $1 {This is the thematic way of
fighting against Black's idea to build a strong centre by means of ...Qc7 and .
..e6-e5.} dxc4 14. Bxc4 Qc7 15. Rac1 {White is better due to his active pieces
and superior development.}) {After} 12. c4 {Black will hardly be able to keep
his position intact.}) 9... Nxg5 10. Nxg5 h6 11. Nf3 Bd6 12. Re1 {White
managed to obtain a classical advantage. As I have pointed out on many
occasions, the structure arising after ...d7-d5 followed by ...cxd4 is always
favourable for White.} ({I would have preferred to liberate the queen by
starting with} 12. Nbd2 Bd7 13. Rb1 {A possible follow up would be} Rc8 14. Qd1
({Even} 14. Qe1 {might be possible in some cases. The queen will go to e2
anyway.}) 14... O-O 15. Re1 $14 ({or} 15. Qe2 $14)) 12... Bd7 13. Nbd2 O-O 14.
Nf1 {[%cal Gf1g3] Transferring the knight to g3 is another thematic idea in
this pawn structure.} ({Once again,} 14. Rb1 Rac8 15. Qd1 {would have been my
preference.}) 14... a6 15. Ng3 {We have reached a position that is typical for
the structures with ...d7-d5 followed by ...cxd4. Since we are already
familiar with all the typical ideas, I will leave the remaining part of the
game without comments. White has a promising attack.} Qc7 16. Qd2 (16. Qe3 Rfe8
