3. Bg5 c5 4. e3 Qb6 (4... d5 5. Nbd2 Qb6 6. Rb1) 5. Qc1 (5. Nbd2) 5... Nc6 6.
c3 d5 {The great Boris Spassky missed the trick with e6-e5! ...however, Black
missed it too...and the game is a wonderfull illustration of the typical Tore
plans!} 7. Nbd2 $2 (7. Bd3) (7. h3 $1 h6 8. Bf4) 7... Bd7 (7... cxd4 $3 8. exd4
e5 $3 $17) 8. Bd3 Rc8 9. O-O cxd4 10. exd4 Bd6 $2 (10... Nb4 $1 11. Be2 Bb5 12.
Qd1 Bxe2 13. Qxe2 Nc6 14. Bxf6 (14. Rab1 Be7 15. Ne1 O-O 16. Nd3) 14... gxf6
15. Rab1 (15. c4)) 11. Re1 $16 {And now...we consolidate..and finally switch
to typical Torre play...with the wrong move by black cxd4?..in connection with
d5 !!} Nh5 (11... Nb4 12. Bb1) (11... O-O 12. Qb1 (12. Ne5) (12. Bxf6 gxf6 13.
Ne4 $3 $18 {is a very forsed win...with our queen, all of the sudden, arriving
on h6!} dxe4 14. Rxe4 f5 15. Qg5+ Kh8 16. Qf6+ Kg8 17. Rg4+ fxg4 18. Bxh7+ Kxh7
19. Ng5+ Kg8 20. Qh6 Bxh2+ 21. Kh1 Rfe8 22. Qh7+ Kf8 23. Qxf7#)) 12. Ne5 Nxe5
13. dxe5 Bc5 14. Be3 Bxe3 15. Rxe3 Nf4 16. Nb3 Bb5 17. Bxb5+ Qxb5 18. Nd4 Qc4
19. Qd1 O-O 20. Qg4 Ng6 21. h4 $18 Kh8 22. h5 Ne7 23. Rg3 Rg8 24. Qg5 Rce8 25.
h6 Ng6 26. f4 Qc7 27. hxg7+ Rxg7 28. Qf6 Qd8 29. f5 exf5 30. Nxf5 Qxf6 31. exf6
Rgg8 32. Nd6 Ref8 33. Re1 Nf4 34. Rxg8+ Kxg8 35. Re7 Nh5 36. Rxb7 Nxf6 37. Rxa7
Ne4 38. Nxe4 dxe4 39. b4 Rd8 40. b5 e3 41. Re7 1-0

