488,491,634,762,895,952,952,1012,1604,2074] A very important chapter in the
Torre is the delayed cxd4 by Black (without d5 of course) Usually when Black
does that...I take cd4! ..and then play on the queenside with
Rac1-Qe2-Rc2-Rfc1 etc...or go for e3-e4! ..depending on the situation!!} 1. d4
Nf6 2. Bg5 e6 (2... Ne4) 3. Nf3 Be7 4. e3 (4. Nbd2) 4... b6 5. Bd3 Bb7 6. Nbd2
d6 7. O-O c5 8. c3 Nbd7 (8... cxd4 9. cxd4 $1 $14 {the most annoying! ....if I
take 9.ed4.. it's fine...but I have lost the plans with Bxf6 and 0-0-0 because
I have already castled short!! .....details!} O-O 10. e4 (10. Qe2)) 9. e4 $1 h6
10. Bf4 (10. Bh4 Nh5 11. Bg3 Nxg3 12. hxg3 $14 e5 13. dxe5 $1 dxe5 14. a4 O-O
