{[%evp 0,101,19,31,14,-9,15,18,12,-11,27,34,46,31,30,25,27,27,33,28,38,25,20,4,
40,48,34,27,15,40,42,15,33,30,52,52,61,19,49,49,118,102,105,81,124,115,116,62,
110,63,93,91,148,155,155,174,174,193,193,169,197,74,94,100,104,104,104,63,66,
80,127,56,77,71,81,81,79,77,288,284,284,284,284,269,325,269,325,325,325,269,
334,339,321,323,321,311,321,315,315,387,395,203,208,154] Great game by two
top-level players in the Tore Attack with h6-g5 and e6. This setup very much
resemples the lines of the g6 Tore and then h6-g5. The best plan for White
seems to be Nc4! followed by Bd3-Qe2..Nfd2-Ne3! White should be carefull with
the move order, depending on our opponents moves!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 e6 3. Nf3
h6 4. Bh4 g5 5. Bg3 Ne4 $6 {it is not easy to critisize Topalov, but I think
this move is already an innacuracy} (5... d6 $1 6. Nbd2 Nh5 {[%cal Rf8g7]
where Black is waiting with Nxg3}) 6. Nbd2 Nxg3 {now this move is forced} 7.
hxg3 Bg7 8. c3 d6 9. e4 a6 (9... Nd7) (9... Nc6) (9... b6) ({I am giving you
this line as an illustrative example of White's idae, if Black just didn't do
anything.} 9... Rh7 10. Nc4 Rh8 11. Bd3 Rh7 12. Qe2 Rh8 13. Ne3 Rh7 14. Nd2 Rh8
15. O-O-O) 10. Bd3 (10. Nc4 $1 {In my opinion, White should start with this
move.} b6 (10... b5 $6 {is wrong, because later White can challenge the
queenside with a2-a4} 11. Ne3) 11. Bd3 Bb7 12. Qe2 Nd7 ({If} 12... Qe7 13.
O-O-O Nd7 14. Kb1 c5 $6 {is very well met by} 15. e5 $1 dxe5 16. dxe5 O-O 17.
Be4 Bxe4+ 18. Qxe4 {with an absolutely winning position. For example:} Rab8 19.
Nxg5 $16) 13. Nfd2 $16) 10... Nd7 11. Qe2 Qe7 12. Nc4 $3 $16 b6 13. Ne3 Bb7 (
13... c5 14. d5 $1 $16) 14. a4 Kf8 (14... O-O $2 {loses immediately after:} 15.
Ng4 $1 $18) 15. Nd2 c5 16. d5 Ne5 ({If} 16... exd5 {White can enter a better
endgame after:} 17. Nxd5 Bxd5 18. exd5 Qxe2+ 19. Bxe2 Re8 20. Kf1 $16 {[%csl
Ra6]}) 17. Bc2 a5 {an ugly move, but Topalov wants to activate his bishop via
a6} 18. Bb3 Ba6 19. Ndc4 f5 20. Nxe5 (20. dxe6 $1 $18) 20... Bxe5 21. Bc4 f4
22. gxf4 gxf4 23. Ng4 Bxc4 (23... Bxc3+ $1 24. bxc3 Qg7 $1 $13) 24. Qxc4 Bg7
25. dxe6 h5 26. Qd5 $18 Re8 27. Qf5+ Kg8 28. Rxh5 Rxh5 29. Qxh5 Qxe6 30. O-O-O
Qxe4 31. Nh6+ Bxh6 32. Qxh6 Re6 33. Qg5+ Kf7 34. Rh1 Rf6 35. Qg4 Qf5 36. Qf3 d5
37. Rh5 Qe4 38. Rxd5 Qxa4 39. Qh5+ Ke6 40. Qe5+ Kf7 41. Qc7+ Kg6 42. Qc8 Qa1+
43. Kc2 Qa4+ 44. Kc1 Qa1+ 45. Kc2 Qa4+ 46. Kd2 Qc6 47. Qg8+ Kh6 48. Qh8+ Kg6
49. Qg8+ Kh6 50. c4 Qe6 51. Qh8+ Kg6 52. Rh5 Qd7+ 53. Kc1 Qe7 54. Kb1 Qe4+ 55.
Ka1 Re6 56. f3 1-0

