12. Bxe7 (12. Bg3 Nxg3 13. hxg3) 12... Qxe7 13. Qe3)) 9. O-O c5 (9... Nh5 10.
Bxe7 {The computer almost always likes this idea.} (10. Bg3 {I like this move
a lot in such positions because I think that my knights are not worse than his
bishops.} Nxg3 11. hxg3 Nd7 12. Re1 (12. Qe2 a6 13. Rfe1)) 10... Qxe7 11. Re1
$14 Nf4 12. Bf1 e5 13. g3 Ng6 14. h4 $14) 10. Re1 Nbd7 11. h3 a6 12. Rc1 Rc8
