{Great performance by the world champion against a very strong opponent.. He
shows the best ideas for White, although its just a blitz game!} 1. d4 Nf6 2.
Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 h6 4. Bh4 d6 5. c3 (5. e4 $2 g5 $1 $19) 5... g5 6. Bg3 Nh5 (6...
Ne4 $6 {is inaccurate because Black should immediately capture on g3.} 7. Nbd2
Nxg3 8. hxg3 $14) 7. e4 Bg7 (7... f5 $2 {almost never works} 8. Nfd2 Nxg3 (8...
Nf6 9. f3 $14) 9. hxg3 $14) 8. Bd3 Nd7 9. Nbd2 b6 10. Qe2 ({an immediate} 10.
Nc4 {is also worth considering}) 10... Bb7 11. Nc4 $1 Qe7 12. Nfd2 $1 Nxg3 13.
hxg3 a6 ({the advance} 13... c5 {is well met by} 14. e5 $1 ({or} 14. d5 exd5
15. Ne3 dxe4 16. Nf5 $14)) 14. f4 d5 15. exd5 Bxd5 16. Ne3 Bb7 17. Be4 {
as we already know, exchanging the lights-squared bishop is in White's favour}
Bxe4 18. Nxe4 f5 19. Nd2 Nf6 20. O-O-O O-O $4 21. Nxf5 {White wins an
important pawn and Korobov immediately resigns} 1-0

