taking with the c-pawn when white's king is already castled} Nc6 11. a3 Rc8 12.
O-O Nh5 13. Bxe7 Nxe7 14. Rfc1) 10... Nc6 (10... Nh5 11. Bg3 Nc6 12. O-O-O (12.
O-O Nxg3 13. hxg3)) (10... Nd5 {this move is dangerous with the bishop on g5.}
11. Bg3 {and White covers the f4-square}) (10... d5 11. O-O $16) 11. Bxf6 Bxf6
12. O-O-O (12. O-O $5 Ne7) 12... Rc8 13. Kb1 Ne7 14. Ne4 (14. h4 Nd5 15. Bc2
Rxc3) 14... Nd5 15. Qd2 Be7 16. h4) 10. O-O Nbd7 (10... cxd4 11. cxd4 Nc6 12.
a3 Rc8 13. Rac1 $14) 11. e4 e5 ({If} 11... Nh5 12. Bg3 {is interesting} (12.
Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Qe3 $1 {remember this typical idea} e5 14. dxe5 dxe5 15. Rfd1 Nf4
16. Bf1 Rfd8 17. g3 $1 Ne6 18. Nc4 $14) 12... Nxg3 13. hxg3 e5 14. dxe5 Nxe5
15. Nxe5 dxe5 16. Rfd1 $14) 12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 dxe5 14. Nc4 Qc7 15. Ne3 g5
(15... Rfd8 16. Bxf6 $6 (16. f3) (16. Rfd1) 16... Bxf6 17. Bc4 (17. f3 Bg5 $1 (
17... Rac8 18. Bc4 (18. Ba6) 18... Bg5 19. Nd5 Bxd5 20. Bxd5) 18. Nd5 (18. Bc4
Bxe3+ 19. Qxe3 Rd6) 18... Bxd5 19. exd5 g6 $15 20. c4 f5 (20... Be7 21. Rae1
Bd6 22. g3 f5 23. Kh1 Re8 24. b3 h5 $1 25. g4 hxg4 26. fxg4 e4)) 17... Bxe4 18.
Ng4 Bg6 19. Nxf6+ gxf6 $15) 16. Bg3 Nxe4 17. Nf5 Nxg3 18. fxg3 Bd5 19. Qh5 e4
20. Qxh6 Qe5 21. Rae1 Rae8 22. Bxe4 Bxe4 23. Rxe4 1-0

