{In the following game we will see the setup with quick b6-Bb7 and Ne4. We
should remember that we have several ways to fight against this setup: 1.To
answer Ne4 with Bc2, preparing Nxe4 2.Challenging the knight on e4, by playing
h4 and Ng5.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 d5 4. e3 Nbd7 (4... c5 5. c3 Nc6 6.
Nbd2 Be7 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O $1 (8. Ne5 $6 Nd7 $1 $132) 8... b6 (8... h6 9. Bh4
b6 10. Ne5 Bb7 11. Bxf6 (11. f4 Nd7 12. Bxe7 (12. Bg3) 12... Qxe7 13. Qh5)
11... Bxf6 12. f4 Rc8 13. Qh5) (8... Nd7 9. Bf4 b6 10. e4 $1 cxd4 (10... Bb7
11. e5 $16 cxd4 12. cxd4 Nb4 13. Be2 (13. Bb1 Ba6 14. a3 Nd3 $1 $132) 13... Ba6
14. Bxa6 Nxa6 15. Qe2 Nab8 16. Rfc1 $16) 11. exd5 exd5 12. Nxd4 $16 (12. cxd4))
9. Ne5 $1 Bb7 (9... Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. f4) 10. f4 (10. Bxf6
Bxf6 11. f4 $16) 10... h6 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. Qh5 $16 Nxe5 13. dxe5 $16 (13. fxe5
$16)) 5. Nbd2 Be7 6. Bd3 b6 7. c3 Bb7 (7... O-O 8. h4 Bb7 (8... h6 9. Ne5 (9.
Bf4 Bb7 10. Qe2 Ne4 11. g4)) 9. Ne5 (9. Qe2) 9... Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. f4 c5
12. Qh5 {provoking g6} g6 13. Qh6 Re8 14. h5 Bxg5 15. fxg5 Nf8 16. hxg6 fxg6
17. Bxg6 $18) 8. h4 $3 {When we reach the position with a fast b6-Bb7-Ne4, I
am following the setup with h4,Bf4,Qe2 ! ...and im ready to challenge the Ne4
with Ng5 ...or to continue in London style...with Rg1 and g4 !!} (8. Qe2 $3 Ne4
(8... c5 9. Bf4 cxd4 10. exd4) 9. Bf4 c5 (9... Nxd2 10. Qxd2 O-O 11. h4 Nf6 12.
Qe2 Ne4 13. g4 c5 14. g5) (9... f5 10. Ne5 $16 O-O 11. Nxd7 Qxd7 12. Nf3 $16)
10. h4 O-O 11. Ng5 $1 $16 (11. g4 $5) (11. Bc2 $1 $16 Rc8 12. Nxe4 dxe4 13. Ng5
Nf6 14. Be5 h6 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Nxe4) 11... Ndf6 12. Be5 $16 (12. Ndxe4 dxe4
13. Bc2 h6 14. Be5 $16)) 8... Ne4 (8... h6 {is always well met by} 9. Bf4 O-O
10. Ne5 c5 11. Ndf3 $3 {the computer favourite} (11. Qf3 $16 {This is the best
human move} Nxe5 12. dxe5 Ne4 13. Nxe4 dxe4 14. Bxe4 Bxe4 15. Qxe4 Qc7 16. h5
Rfd8 17. Ke2 $14 {White is a pawn up without any compensation.}) 11... Ne4 12.
Nxd7 Qxd7 13. Ne5 Qc8 14. Qg4 $18 Nf6 15. Qe2 Ne4 16. f3 Nd6 17. g4 $16) 9. Bf4
c5 10. Qe2 (10. g4) (10. Bc2 {the computer likes this idea very much. The idea
is to take Nxe4.} O-O 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Ng5 Nf6 (12... cxd4 13. exd4 Nf6 14.
Qe2 Nd5 15. Qxe4) 13. Be5 h6 14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. Bxe4 $16 {with a healthy pawn
up.} (15. Nxe4 $16)) 10... a6 11. h5 $5 (11. Bc2 $3 {preparing Nxe4 !} b5 12.
Nxe4 dxe4 13. Nd2 $16 (13. Ng5 Nf6 14. Be5 $16) 13... f5 (13... Nf6 14. Be5)
14. O-O-O $3) 11... h6 12. Ne5 $1 (12. Bc2 $3) 12... O-O 13. Nxd7 Qxd7 14. Nf3
Bd6 15. Ne5 Bxe5 16. Bxe5 f5 17. f3 Ng5 18. f4 Ne4 19. Bxe4 fxe4 20. g4 $16 Qb5
21. Rg1 Qxe2+ 22. Kxe2 Kf7 23. g5 Rg8 24. Rg3 Bc6 25. Rag1 cxd4 26. Bxd4 Raf8
27. gxh6 gxh6 28. Rg7+ Rxg7 29. Rxg7+ Ke8 30. Rg6 Bb5+ 31. Kf2 Rf5 32. Rxe6+
Kd7 33. Rxh6 Bc4 34. b3 Bd3 35. Rh8 Ke6 36. Bxb6 Bb1 37. a4 Bc2 38. Bd4 Bxb3
39. a5 Bc4 40. Kg3 Be2 41. Kh4 Kf7 42. Be5 Ke6 43. h6 Rh5+ 44. Kg3 Kf7 45. Kf2
Bf3 46. Kg3 Be2 47. Kf2 Bc4 48. Bg7 Kg6 49. Rf8 Rh3 50. f5+ Kg5 51. f6 Rf3+ 52.
Kg2 Rxe3 53. h7 Kg4 54. h8=Q Re2+ 55. Kg1 Re1+ 56. Kh2 Re2+ 57. Kh1 Re1+ 58.
Kh2 Re2+ 59. Kh1 Re1+ 60. Kh2 1/2-1/2

