{[%evp 0,73,20,17,20,19,19,18,18,3,20,11,12,8,15,-4,10,-11,30,2,36,17,32,28,28,
42,37,9,53,54,63,63,66,59,99,112,219,218,219,188,190,185,206,171,209,214,200,
184,183,212,195,189,190,178,182,180,199,187,236,241,259,217,260,261,227,236,
295,311,305,310,330,368,352,277,288,311] In the following game we will se the
plan with d5,Be7, 0-0 for Black. The correct way for White to handle this
position is to delay short castle} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 d5 4. e3 Be7 (
4... c5 5. Nbd2 Nbd7 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O h6 9. Bh4 Qc7 (9... b6 10. Qe2
Bb7 11. e4 dxe4 12. Bxe4 Qc7 13. Bxb7 Qxb7 14. Nc4 Bc7 (14... Be7 15. a4 Rac8
16. Rfd1 cxd4 (16... Rfd8 17. d5) 17. Nxd4 a6 (17... Qa6 18. Nb5) 18. h3 Rfe8 (
18... Rfd8 19. Nxe6) 19. Nf3 Qc7 20. Ne3 Qb7) 15. dxc5 Nxc5 16. Bxf6 gxf6 17.
Nd4 Qe4 18. Qh5) 10. Rc1 b6 11. c4 Bb7 12. cxd5 exd5 13. b3 Rfe8 (13... Rac8
14. Bf5) 14. Bg3 (14. Bf5) 14... Bxg3 15. hxg3 Rad8 16. Qc2 Qd6 17. Qb2) 5.
Nbd2 (5. c4 {This move takes us to QGD} O-O 6. Nc3) 5... O-O 6. Bd3 Nbd7 (6...
c5 7. c3 Nc6 (7... Nbd7 8. Ne5) 8. O-O (8. Ne5 Nd7) 8... b6 9. Ne5 Nxe5 10.
dxe5 Nd7 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. f4 f6 13. exf6 Rxf6 (13... Qxf6 14. e4) (13... Nxf6
14. Nf3) 14. e4) 7. c3 $3 {A VERY USEFULL WAITING MOVE! ...we dont castle yet
in the d5-Nbd7-Be7 system...because the rook has a lot of potential on h1 ,
connected with h4-f4-hg5 or Rh3-Rg3 ideas !!!} (7. Ne5 $6 Nxe5 8. dxe5 Nd7 9.
Bxe7 Qxe7 10. f4 Nc5 $3 $132 {this is the difference ! Now black can use c5
square for his knight! That's why we do not hurry with 7.Ne5 but, we play 7.c3!
waiting for our opponent to play c5 and occupy this square with a pawn !!})
7... c5 (7... b6 $1 {SUPER SOS ...AN IMPORTANT VARIATION....HOW TO DEAL WITH
THE SIMPLE PLAN OF Bb7 and Ne4  ????...here is how! ..with Qe2-Bf4-Ng5!!
challenging the knight on e4 !!! (PAP) .....we can start by Qe2 first..or h4
first...the move order doesnt relly matter....just dont be in a hurry to
castle when you see d5-Nbd7 and Be7 !!!} 8. h4 $3 ({Premature is} 8. Ne5 $6
Nxe5 (8... Bb7 $6 {is a mistake} 9. h4 $14 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. f4 (11. Bf4)
11... Nc5 12. Bc2 Ba6 13. Nb3 $3 Ne4 14. Qf3 Bb7 15. Nd2 $16) 9. dxe5 Nd7 10.
Bxe7 (10. Bf4 Nc5 11. Bc2 Ba6) 10... Qxe7 11. f4 Nc5 12. Bc2 Ba6 13. Nb3 Ne4
14. Qf3 $132) (8. Qe2 $3 {Is a good waiting move, preparing 0-0-0. Now White
will continue with h4 and Bf4} Bb7 9. h4 {The king on "e1" is very safe, so we
can start an attack immediately} Ne4 (9... c5 10. Ne5 $1 {after c7-c5 , there
is no Nd7-Nc5 !!} (10. g4 $5) (10. Bf4 $1) 10... Nxe5 11. dxe5 Nd7 12. f4 $3 h6
13. Qh5 $18) 10. Bf4 c5 11. Ng5 $1 (11. g4 $1) 11... Ndf6 12. Be5 $16) 8... Bb7
9. Qe2 $3 (9. Ne5 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. f4 (11. Bf4) 11... Nc5 12. Bc2) 9... c5
(9... Ne4 10. Bf4 c5 (10... h6 11. g4) 11. Ng5 (11. g4) 11... Ndf6 12. Be5) 10.
Ne5) 8. Ne5 $1 (8. Qe2 $1 {is also very good !!! ...i repeat...in the
d5-bd7-Be7 Tore....DO NOT BE IN A HURRY TO CASTLE SHORT!!} b6 9. h4 $1 (9. Ne5
$1 $36 Bb7 10. h4 Ne4 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. Nxd7 Qxd7 13. h5) 9... Bb7 10. Bf4 Ne4
11. Ng5 $1 (11. g4) 11... Ndf6 12. Be5 $16) 8... Re8 $2 {is a well known
mistake. Now White continues with f4 with an advantage.} (8... h6 9. Bf4 $3 (9.
h4 $3 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. f4 f6 12. Bxh6 gxh6 13. Qg4+) 9... Nxe5 10. dxe5
Nd7 11. Qh5 Bg5 (11... f6 12. Qg6 f5 13. Qxe6+) 12. g3 $3 g6 13. Qe2 Kg7 14. h4
Be7 15. e4 $16 d4 16. cxd4 cxd4 17. Nf3) (8... Nxe5 $1 9. dxe5 Nd7 10. Bxe7
Qxe7 11. f4 f6 12. Qh5 (12. exf6 $1 Rxf6 13. O-O e5 14. Bc2 $3) 12... g6 (12...
f5 13. g4 $16) 13. Qh4 Qg7 (13... g5 14. exf6) 14. exf6 Qxf6 (14... Nxf6 15.
Nf3 $16 (15. O-O $16)) 15. Qxf6 Rxf6 (15... Nxf6 16. Nf3) 16. Nf3 e5 17. fxe5
Re6 18. c4 (18. O-O-O $3 {computer} Nxe5 19. Be2 Ng4 20. Rxd5) 18... Nxe5 19.
Nxe5 Rxe5 20. cxd5 Rxe3+ (20... Bf5)) 9. f4 $1 (9. O-O $5 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11.
Bxe7 Qxe7 12. f4 f6 13. exf6 $1 Qxf6 (13... Nxf6 14. Nf3 $14) 14. e4 $14) 9...
Nf8 10. h4 $3 (10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. O-O Be7 12. Qh5 g6 13. Qh6 Bf6) (10. O-O N6d7
11. Bxe7 (11. Qh5 g6 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Qh3 f6 14. Nef3 e5) 11... Qxe7 12. Qh5 (
12. Qc2 f6 13. Nxd7 Bxd7) 12... f6 13. Nxd7 Bxd7) 10... h6 (10... N6d7 11. Qh5
g6 (11... Nxe5 12. fxe5 (12. dxe5) 12... g6 13. Qh6 Bxg5 14. hxg5 Bd7 15. Nf3
c4 16. Bc2 b5 17. Nh2 {[%cal Rh2g4,Rg4f6] with mate to follow}) (11... f6 12.
Bxh7+ $3 {is a well known tactical idea.} Nxh7 13. Qf7+ Kh8 14. Ng6#) 12. Qh6
f6 13. h5 Nxe5 (13... fxe5 14. hxg6 e4 15. Nxe4 (15. gxh7+ Kh8 16. Qg7+ Kxg7
17. h8=Q+ Kf7 18. Rh7+ Nxh7 (18... Kg6 19. Rg7+ Kf5 20. Qh3#) 19. Qxh7+ Kf8 20.
Bh6#) 15... dxe4 16. Bxe4) 14. dxe5 fxg5 15. hxg6 Qc7 16. g7 (16. gxh7+ Kh8 17.
Qg7+) 16... Bd8 17. Bxh7+ $18) 11. Bxf6 $1 (11. Qf3 $3 {This is the best move
according to the engine.}) 11... Bxf6 (11... gxf6 12. Qg4+ Kh8 13. Nxf7#) 12.
Qh5 Qe7 (12... g6 13. Qf3 $3 (13. Qg4 Bg7 14. h5 g5 15. Ndf3 f5 {and Black is
quite safe.}) (13. Qxh6 Bg7 14. Qg5 f6 15. Qg3 fxe5 16. fxe5 Bh6 $15) 13... Bg7
(13... h5 14. g4 Bxh4+ 15. Ke2 $40) 14. h5 g5 15. fxg5 Bxe5 16. gxh6 cxd4 17.
exd4 Bf6 18. O-O Nd7 19. Bb5 $18) 13. Ng4 $3 (13. Ndf3 g6 14. Qxh6 (14. Qg4)
14... Bg7 15. Qg5 f6 16. Qg3 fxe5 17. fxe5 Bh6) 13... cxd4 (13... Nd7 14. Nf3
g6 15. Qxh6 (15. Nxf6+ Nxf6 16. Qxh6 Ng4) 15... Bg7 16. Qg5 f6 17. Qxg6 Nf8 18.
