{This is classical game between two great players which I decided to include
in my lecture.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 d5 4. Nbd2 Be7 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Bd3 c5
7. c3 b6 (7... O-O 8. Ne5 $1 h6 9. Bf4 $1 (9. h4 $1)) (7... Qc7 $1 {Is
probably the most promising plan for Black} 8. O-O O-O 9. Rc1 $3 b6 10. c4 Bb7
11. cxd5 exd5 12. b3 $1 $14) 8. O-O $6 {As I mentioned before , in the setup
with e6-d5-Nbd7 and Be7, WE SHOULD NOT BE IN A HURRY TO CASTLE! We should play
moves like Qe2-h4-Bf4! If he didn't to anything I can include a Ne5 move!!} (8.
Ne5 $5 {this is alo interesting..but keep in mind that black may try to castle
long! ...just like in this famous game!} Nxe5 (8... Bb7 9. Bb5 (9. f4 O-O 10.
Qf3) 9... O-O 10. Nc6) 9. dxe5 Nd7 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. f4 Bb7 12. O-O O-O-O (
12... f6 13. exf6) 13. Qe2 $1 Kb8 (13... g5 14. Ba6 $16 Rhg8 15. Bxb7+ (15. a4)
15... Kxb7 16. a4 (16. c4)) 14. Ba6 Ba8 15. a4 $16 f6 16. exf6 gxf6 17. a5 Rhg8
18. axb6 axb6 19. e4 $16 (19. Bb5 $16)) (8. Qe2 $1 Bb7 9. h4 O-O 10. Bf4 $1 (
10. Rg1 $5) 10... Ne4 11. Ng5 $16 (11. Bc2 $1 $36) 11... Ndf6 12. Be5 $14) 8...
Bb7 (8... Qc7 9. Rc1) 9. Ne5 (9. a4 $5) 9... Nxe5 $1 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Bf4 $2 {
This is totally wrong. White expects Black to castle short.} (11. Bxe7 $142 $1
{is the correct strategy for White} Qxe7 12. f4 O-O (12... O-O-O 13. Qe2 f6 14.
exf6 gxf6 15. Ba6 Rhg8 16. a4 c4 17. Bxb7+ Kxb7 18. e4 $14) 13. Nf3 $1 {
is the correct move} (13. e4 $10) (13. Qh5 $1 g6 (13... f5 14. Nf3 a6 15. g4
$16 g6 16. Qh6) 14. Qh3 f6 15. exf6 Nxf6 16. Nf3) 13... f6 (13... c4 14. Bc2
Nc5 15. Nd4 Ne4 16. Bxe4 (16. Rf3 Rad8 17. Bxe4 dxe4 18. Rh3) 16... dxe4 17.
Kh1) 14. exf6 Nxf6 (14... Rxf6 15. Bb5 $1 (15. Qc2 h6 16. Nh4) (15. Bc2) 15...
a6 16. Bxd7 Qxd7 17. Ne5 Qe7 18. Rf2 Kh8 19. b4 Rc8 20. bxc5 Rxc5 21. Rb2 b5
22. Qd4 (22. a4)) 15. Qe1 Nd7 16. Qg3 $16 (16. Bb5 $16) 16... e5 $2 17. fxe5
$18 (17. Nxe5 $18) 17... Rae8 18. Ng5 h6 19. e6 $18) 11... Qc7 (11... g5 $6 12.
Bg3 h5 13. h3) 12. Nf3 (12. Qg4 $2 g5 13. Bxg5 Rg8 14. h4 h6 $19) 12... h6 $1
13. b4 g5 $1 14. Bg3 h5 (14... cxb4 $2 15. cxb4 Bxb4 16. Nd4) 15. h4 gxh4 $1 (
15... g4 16. Ne1 Nxe5 17. Bb5+ Kf8 18. bxc5 bxc5 19. Qa4 $16) 16. Bf4 (16. Nxh4
$2 c4 17. Bc2 Bxh4 18. Bxh4 Qxe5 $17) 16... O-O-O $1 17. a4 $2 (17. bxc5 $5
bxc5 18. Rb1 $13) 17... c4 $1 18. Be2 (18. Bf5 $5 {e.g. 18...} exf5 19. e6 Bd6
20. exd7+ Rxd7 21. Qd4) 18... a6 $1 19. Kh1 (19. b5 {PAP} a5 20. Nd4 Nxe5 21.
Nc6 Bd6 (21... Bxc6 22. bxc6 Bd6 23. Rb1 Qxc6 24. Qd4 Nd7) 22. Nxd8 Rxd8 23.
Bxh5 Rg8) 19... Rdg8 20. Rg1 Rg4 21. Qd2 (21. Nh2 $5 Rg6 22. Nf3 Rhg8 23. Qd2)
21... Rhg8 22. a5 b5 23. Rad1 Bf8 $1 {[/\ 24...f6 25.exf6 e5]} 24. Nh2 Nxe5 $1
25. Nxg4 hxg4 26. e4 Bd6 (26... dxe4 $4 27. Bxe5 $16) 27. Qe3 Nd7 (27... g3 $5
28. f3 $1) 28. Bxd6 Qxd6 29. Rd4 $2 (29. f4 $1 f5 30. e5 Qc7) 29... e5 $1 30.
Rd2 (30. Rxd5 $5 Bxd5 31. Rd1 Nf6 32. exd5 $15) 30... f5 $1 $17 31. exd5 (31.
exf5 h3 $1 $17) (31. exf5 Nf6 $1 32. f3 Nh5 33. fxg4 Ng3+ 34. Kh2 d4 $1 $17)
31... f4 $1 32. Qe4 (32. Qa7 e4 $17) 32... Nf6 33. Qf5+ Kb8 34. f3 (34. Qe6
Qxe6 35. dxe6 Ne4 $1 $17) 34... Bc8 35. Qb1 g3 36. Re1 h3 37. Bf1 (37. gxh3 g2+
38. Kg1 Qd7 $1 $19) 37... Rh8 38. gxh3 Bxh3 39. Kg1 (39. Bxh3 Qd7 $1) 39...
Bxf1 40. Kxf1 (40. Rxf1 Qd7 {/\ 41...Qh3 or 41...Qa7+}) 40... e4 $1 41. Qd1 (
41. fxe4 f3 $1 $19) 41... Ng4 $1 42. fxg4 f3 43. Rg2 fxg2+ {[44.Kxg2 Qf4]} 0-1

