{a very instructive analysis in the Nbd7 -Be7 system} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. d4 e6 3.
Bg5 Be7 4. Nbd2 d5 5. e3 O-O 6. Bd3 Nbd7 {There is a rule of thumb here. When
you see Nbd7 and 0-0, White should delay 0-0 and sometimes goes for 0-0-0.
White's idea is Ne5 followed by f4 in an appropriate momment.} (6... c5 7. c3
Nbd7 (7... Nc6 8. O-O b6 9. Ne5 Bb7 10. f4 Nxe5 11. fxe5 Ne4 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13.
Bxe4 (13. Qc2) 13... dxe4 14. Qg4 cxd4 15. exd4 e3 16. Ne4 $18) (7... cxd4 $2
8. exd4) 8. Ne5 $3 (8. O-O b6 9. Ne5) 8... h6 $2 (8... Qc7 9. f4) (8... Nxe5 9.
dxe5 Nd7 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. f4 b6 (11... f6 12. exf6 Nxf6 13. Nf3) 12. O-O Bb7
13. Nf3 (13. Qe1 f6 14. exf6 (14. Qh4) 14... Nxf6 (14... Qxf6 15. e4) (14...
Rxf6 15. e4) 15. Qh4 (15. Nf3 Nd7 16. Bb5) 15... Rad8 16. Bxh7+)) 9. h4 $3 (9.
Bf4 $3 b6 10. h4 Bb7 11. Qf3 (11. g4 Nxe5 12. dxe5 Ne4 13. Bxe4 dxe4 14. g5)
11... Nxe5 12. dxe5 Nd7 13. Qh5 (13. Qg4 $3 Kh8 14. Qh5 $3) 13... f5 14. g4)
9... Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. f4 $3 b6 (11... hxg5 12. hxg5 Bxg5 13. fxg5 Qxg5 14.
Bh7+ (14. Qf3 Rd8) 14... Kh8 15. Qe2 Nxe5 16. O-O-O $18 g6 17. Bxg6+) 12. Qh5
f5 (12... Bb7 13. Bxh6) 13. Bxh6) 7. c3 $1 {This is a very good waiting move
and the best try for White.} (7. Ne5 {is a bit premature here} h6 (7... Nxe5 8.
dxe5 Nd7 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. f4 c5 11. c3 f6 12. exf6 (12. Qh5 g6 13. Qh4) 12...
Nxf6 13. Nf3) (7... Nxe5 8. dxe5 Nd7 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. f4 c5 (10... Nc5) 11. c3)
8. h4 Ne8 9. f4 c5 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. c3) (7. O-O $6 {as we already said, White
needs to delay castling.} b6 8. Ne5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Nd7 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. f4 Nc5
$11) 7... c5 $6 (7... a6 {If Black waits White should continue with Ne5} 8. Ne5
Nxe5 9. dxe5 Nd7 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. f4 Nc5 (11... c5 12. O-O c4 13. Bc2 $16 {
[%cal Rd2f3,Rf3d4,Rf1f3]}) 12. Bc2 $14 {the difference is that White has the
c2-square for his bishop}) (7... h6 8. Bh4 (8. Bf4 Nh5 (8... b6 9. Ne5 Bb7 10.
Qf3) 9. Be5 Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Nf6 11. f4 b6 12. O-O Bb7 13. Qf3) 8... c5 9. Ne5
Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. f4) 8. Ne5 h6 $2 {a very typical mistake} (
8... Nxe5 9. dxe5 Nd7 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. f4 b6 12. O-O $14) 9. Bf4 $3 $16 {
We transpose to London System. This position is considered by the theory as
very dangerous for Black, because the h6-pawn can be used as a hook.} (9. Bh4)
(9. h4 $3 $16 Nxe5 (9... b6 10. f4 Bb7 11. Qf3 Rc8 12. g4 Nxe5 13. fxe5 Ne4 (
13... Nd7 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. g5) 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. Nxe4) 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. f4 $3
d4 (11... f6 12. Bxh6 gxh6 13. Qg4+ Kh8 14. Qg6 f5 15. Qxh6+ Kg8 16. Qxe6+) 12.
Nc4 $16 (12. exd4 cxd4 13. cxd4 $18 f6 14. Bxh6 $18) 12... dxc3 13. bxc3 $16)
9... Nxe5 (9... a5 10. h4 a4 11. a3 Qb6 12. Rb1 Re8 13. g4 $18) 10. dxe5 Nd7
11. Qh5 (11. h4) 11... Bg5 (11... f5 12. g4 Qe8 13. Qxe8 Rxe8 14. gxf5 exf5 15.
Bxf5) 12. g3 $3 g6 13. Qe2 $16 1-0

