{SUPER SUPER SOS GAME!!! Black played the setup with Nbd7-Qc7! The idea is to
STOP ANY Ne5 IDEAS ONCE AND FOR ALL! However the queen is exposed on "c7" and
we must play Rc1 followed by c4. White wants to reach a structure with hanging
pawns in the centre. The game very different than the usual Tore. The system
is objecitevely not bad for Black, but he should know well what he is doing!!} 
1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 c5 4. c3 d5 5. e3 Nbd7 (5... Nc6 6. Nbd2 Be7 7. Bd3
O-O 8. O-O Qc7 {The same idea as in the game doesn't work with the knight on
"c6"} 9. dxc5 {White can use that the f6-knight is not protected and play} ({or
} 9. Bxf6 Bxf6 10. dxc5 Qe7 (10... Be7 11. b4) 11. Nb3 a5 12. a4 e5 13. e4 Be6
14. Qc2 Rab8 15. Rfd1 dxe4 16. Bxe4 Bxb3 17. Qxb3 $14) 9... Bxc5 10. Bxf6 gxf6
11. e4 $36) (5... Nc6 6. Nbd2 Bd6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O h6 (8... h6 9. Bh4 e5 10.
dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. f4 Bd6 13. e4 dxe4 14. Bxf6) (8... h6 9. Bh4 e5 10.
e4 cxd4 11. cxd4) (8... e5 9. e4) 9. Bh4 cxd4 10. exd4 e5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12.
Nxe5 Bxe5 13. Nf3) 6. Nbd2 Be7 (6... Bd6 $5 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O e5 $2 {this move
is totally wrong here} 9. e4 $3 $16 (9. dxe5 $1 {I knew for several years that
White is better after the following forced line} Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Bxe5 11. f4 Bd6
12. e4 dxe4 (12... Be7 13. e5) 13. Bxf6 Qxf6 $4 14. Nxe4 Qe7 15. Nxd6 Qxd6 16.
Bxh7+ $18)) 7. Bd3 Qc7 $1 (7... b6 8. Ne5 $1 $14 (8. Qe2 $1) 8... Nxe5 9. dxe5
Nd7 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. f4 Bb7 12. O-O O-O 13. Nf3 (13. Qh5)) (7... O-O {we
already know that after this move White is much better after:} 8. Ne5 $1 b6 9.
f4 (9. Nc6 Qe8 10. Nxe7+ Qxe7 11. O-O) 9... Bb7 10. Qf3 $14) 8. O-O O-O 9. Qe2
$1 {this is also a good idea, but anyway White needs to contunue with Rc1} (9.
Rc1 $3 {Is the strongest move. This move is strong when Black can't play Ne5
and Black's queen is on "c7"} b6 {If Black didn't play c5-c4, then White is
opening the queenside by means of c3-c4} (9... c4 $5 10. Bb1 b5 11. Bf4 $1 (11.
e4 dxe4 12. Nxe4 Bb7 13. Re1 $132) 11... Bd6 (11... Qb6 12. Ne5 Bb7 13. Qf3 (
13. Bg5 Rad8 14. f4) 13... a5 14. Qh3) 12. Bxd6 Qxd6 13. e4 dxe4 14. Nxe4 Qb6 (
14... Nxe4 15. Bxe4 Rb8 16. Re1 Nf6 17. Bc2 Bb7 18. Ne5 Rfd8 $6 (18... Qd5 19.
f3 Rfd8 20. Qe2 $14) 19. Re3 $1 g6 (19... Qd5 20. Rg3 g6 21. h4 $16) 20. Rg3
Qf8 21. Qd2 Qg7 22. Re1 $16 Bd5 23. h4 $14) 15. Nxf6+ Nxf6 16. Qe2 Bb7 17. Ne5
Rac8 18. Rce1 Rfd8 19. Qd2 $16 (19. f4 $16) 19... a6 20. Qf4) (9... cxd4 $2 10.
exd4 $3 $16 Qb6 11. Rb1) 10. c4 Bb7 (10... dxc4 11. Nxc4 $14 Bb7 12. e4) 11.
cxd5 exd5 12. b3 $3 $14 (12. dxc5) 12... Rac8 (12... Rfe8 13. Bf4 Bd6 14. Bxd6
Qxd6 15. Qc2 Rac8 16. Qb2 $14 Qe7 (16... a6 17. Rfd1 b5 18. dxc5) 17. Rfd1 Ne4
(17... h6 18. Nf1 Nf8 19. Ng3) 18. Nf1 $1 g6 19. Bb5 Red8 20. Bxd7 (20. Ng3
Nxg3 21. hxg3) 20... Rxd7 21. dxc5 bxc5 22. Ng3) 13. Bf5 $14 g6 14. Bh3) (9. a4
b6 10. a5 Bb7 $132) (9. Bf4 $6 {is well met by} Bd6 $11) 9... b6 $1 (9... e5 $2
