{One of the best systems for Black is connected with Bd6-Nbd7 and b6. In the
following game we should see how to react against it.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 d5 3.
Nd2 Nbd7 4. Ngf3 h6 5. Bh4 e6 6. e3 c5 7. c3 Bd6 (7... Be7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. Ne5
Nxe5 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. f4) (7... Be7 8. Bd3 Qc7 9. O-O O-O 10. Rc1
b6 11. c4 Bb7 12. cxd5 exd5 13. b3 Rac8 14. Bg3 Bd6 15. Bxd6 Qxd6 16. Re1 $14 {
[%cal Rd2f1,Rf1g3,Re1e2,Re2c2]}) 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O b6 {This is a very good
system. White needs to play very accurate in order to fight for an advantage.}
(9... e5 10. e4 (10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. f4 Bd6 (12... Bc7 13. e4) 13.
e4 Be7 14. e5)) 10. Qe2 $1 Bb7 (10... cxd4 11. exd4) (10... e5 11. e4) (10...
Qc7 11. Rac1) 11. e4 dxe4 (11... cxd4 $4 {doesn't work due to} 12. e5 dxc3 13.
bxc3) 12. Bxe4 Qc7 (12... Bxe4 {Black can simplify the game, but White keeps
some small advantage after:} 13. Nxe4 Be7 14. Bxf6 Nxf6 15. Nxf6+ Bxf6 16. dxc5
bxc5 17. Nd2 (17. Rad1) 17... Qc7 18. Nc4 $14) 13. Bxb7 Qxb7 14. Nc4 Be7 (14...
Bc7 15. dxc5 bxc5 (15... Nxc5 16. Bxf6 gxf6 $14) 16. Rfd1 $14) 15. a4 $1 {
I think this is the best chance for White. I am providing you with some long
analysys against all Black options} (15. Rfe1 b5 16. Nce5 Nxe5 17. dxe5 Nd5 18.
Bxe7 Nxe7 19. Nd2) 15... Qa6 (15... Rac8 16. Rfd1 Qa6 (16... Rfd8 $4 17. d5 $3
$18) (16... cxd4 17. Nxd4 a6 18. h3 Rfe8 19. Nc2 Bf8 (19... Nc5 20. Bxf6) (
19... Qc7 20. N2e3) (19... Qc6 20. N4e3 (20. N2e3) 20... Qb7 (20... Bf8) 21.
Nb4 a5 22. Nbc2 Nc5 23. Nd4) 20. N2e3 Ne4 (20... b5 21. Nd6 Bxd6 22. Rxd6 Ne4
23. Rd4 Ndc5 24. Rb4) 21. Rxd7) 17. Nfe5 cxd4 (17... Rfd8 18. Nxf7) 18. Nxd7
Nxd7 19. Bxe7 Rfe8 20. Rxd4 Rxe7 21. Rad1 Nf6 22. b3 Ree8 (22... Rec7 23. Rd8+)
23. Qf3 Rf8 24. h3 Nd5 25. R1d3 $18 Rc7 26. Qg3 Rd7 27. Rh4) (15... Rfe8 16. a5
(16. dxc5 Nxc5 17. Bxf6 gxf6 18. Rfe1) 16... b5 17. a6 Qc8 18. Nce5) (15...
Rfd8 16. Rfd1 cxd4 (16... Rac8 17. d5) (16... Nf8 17. Bxf6 Bxf6 18. dxc5 bxc5
19. a5 (19. Nfd2) 19... Rab8 20. Rxd8 Rxd8 21. a6 Qb5 22. g3) 17. Nxd4 a6 (
17... Rac8 18. Nf5 (18. Nb5)) 18. h3 Rac8 (18... Bc5 19. Nb3 (19. Rd3) 19...
Bf8 20. Rd4 Qc6 (20... Rac8 21. Rad1) 21. Rad1 Rdc8 22. Ne3) 19. Nxe6 fxe6 20.
Qxe6+ Kf8 21. Bxf6 gxf6 (21... Nxf6 22. Ne5) 22. Nd6) (15... Rfe8 16. dxc5 Bxc5
