1. d4 Nf6 (1... c5 $2 2. d5 {n even more improved version of the line for
white...because we havent even played Nf3 so we can also use our -f- pawn !...
..} d6 3. e4 Nf6 4. Nc3 g6 5. f4 $16) 2. Nf3 c5 3. d5 b5 {this is supposed to
be the best...but white still has good chances to take the initiative!} (3...
d6 {this is the same with 3...g6 4.Nc3! etc} 4. Nc3 $1 {saving c4 square for
our knight!} g6 (4... e5 $6 5. e4 $16 Bg4 6. Be2 Bxf3 (6... Be7 7. Nd2) 7. Bxf3
Nbd7 8. O-O $16) 5. e4 Bg7 (5... Bg4 6. Be2 Bxf3 (6... Bg7 7. Nd2 Bxe2 8. Qxe2
O-O 9. O-O Nbd7 10. Nc4 (10. a4) 10... Nb6 11. Bg5 (11. Ne3 $1 Qc7 (11... e6
